REASONING: Authoritative sources state the United States consists of 50 states, not 51. Wikipedia: "The United States of America is a federal republic consisting of 50 states, a federal district (Washington, D.C., ...)." (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_states_and_territories_of_the_United_States).
Encyclopaedia Britannica also describes the U.S. as "a federal republic of 50 states," confirming the count of 50 (https://www.britannica.com/place/United-States).

A U.S. government source (USGS) explicitly uses the phrasing "United States: The 50 States and the District of Columbia," showing the official usage of 50 states (https://www.usgs.gov/faqs/what-constitutes-united-states-what-are-official-definitions).
Because multiple reliable references (encyclopedic and government) agree on 50 states, the claim that there are 51 states in America is incorrect.
